Two people were killed and 11 injured when the matatu they were travelling in plunged into Sondu Miriu River on Tuesday afternoon.
The public service vehicle bound for Kisumu veered off Kisii-Kisumu road at about 1pm as the driver swerved to avoid colliding head-on with a lorry.
It ended up in the river as Sondu Bridge does not have guard rails.



