Kericho County Police Commander Silas Gichunge said the matatu’s driver died at the scene and a front seat passenger on the way to St Joseph’s Nyabondo Mission Hospital.
"The matatu driver tried to avoid the oncoming lorry but hit it on the side before the vehicle plunged into the river," said Mr Gichunge.
Felix Ochieng Odhiambo, who is in charge of the hospital, said the casualties taken to the hospital included children.
"Eight were admitted here while three were referred to Aga Khan Hospital in Kisumu," he said.



