The three were a mother and her two children.
One of the patients was in a critical condition, having sustained a head injury.
Plans to rush the patient to the Jaramogi Oginga Odinga Teaching and Referral Hospital in Kisumu were delayed by the nurses’ strike which has disrupted services at public facilities.
Sondu resident Rebecca Kemunto asked the government to repair the bridge.
"It is very narrow and has no guard rails. Contractors working on the road should repair it," she said.
